known of him before his appearance there in 15193 when he supervised Cratander’s edition of Craston’s Greek Dictionary (Ep. 1460 introd.), and matriculated at the University. In 1519 he became a citizen, and in 1521 started printing. A quarrel that he had with Cratander, who had reprinted one of his later editions of Craston, moved the Basle Council to give their citizen- printers copyright for their books for three years. Curio's last book is dated March 1532. His widow married again with John Valderus, and later with Leon. Hospinianus, both printers at Basle. See C. C.
